\b \cf0 One sentence: \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1
\ls2\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 Modern moralities are a mere simulacrum of morality, fragments of an older (largely Aristotelian/Christian) tradition of virtue. That tradition most broadly understood, with its practices and its awareness of the narrative unity of human life, is the only alternative that does not fold under the Nietzschean critique of emotivism, rational morality. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\sb360\sa80
\ls2\ilvl0
\b \cf0 Precis by Chapter: \
\pard\tx360\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 1.	A Disquieting Suggestion\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 Morality today is characterized by a complete lack of understanding of what morality is, what its guts are. The torn pieces of the one-whole garment are, each in isolation, unintelligible to each other and to themselves. \
\pard\tx360\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b \cf3 2.	The Nature of Moral Disagreement Today\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 It is shrill as if no agreement or authority exists, yet loud as if agreement could be reached.\
\pard\tx360\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b \cf3 3.	Emotivism: Social Content and Social Context\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 Moore is just as much an emotivist or proto-emotivist as Mackie, just in a different way. He masks the inability to ground morality in intuitionism. Nietzsche will tear off that mask just as much as he will tear off the mask of Kant and the rationalists. \
\pard\tx360\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b \cf3 4.	The Predecessor Culture and the Enlightenment Project of Justifying Morality\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\tx360\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b \cf3 5.	Why the Enlightenment Project of Justifying Morality Had to Fail\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 It had to fail because it rejected telos, which of the three parts of morality (man as he is, man as he should be, and the practices man needs in order to become what we should) is the part that makes virtue intelligible. \
\pard\tx360\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sl360\slmult1
